When Grayson and I first met he was finishing his first full pro ball season, in A ball with the Tigers. He lived in Lakeland, FL in a house full of teammates and I was still in college. I honestly had no clue where Michigan was on a map at that point or how the minor league system worked... I also had no idea what a wild ride and incredible blessing baseball would be for us 💛

Throughout Grayson’s career we traveled all over the country, to Canada and the Dominican. We stayed in some of the cheapest hotels in miscellaneous minor league towns and some of the most incredible 5 stars in amazing big league cities. We moved countless times all over the place, met many wonderful people, and made endless memories. 

There are so many moments I’ll never forget.. Getting engaged on an off day when he was in double A. Taking Hudson to his first ever baseball game at only a month old. The moment we found out Grayson was going to the big leagues and how dang nervous I was at his debut 💛 Finding out he was going to be the starting catcher for the Detroit Tigers. Opening Day where it dumped snow and I was pregnant with Hayes… the list could go on and I wish I could go back to savor each of those moments a little bit more. 

Grayson, I’m incredibly proud of you!! You did it, you made your lifelong dream come true ⭐️ Decades of dedication, sacrifices and grit got you to the place you’re at today. The little tee ball player who dreamed of being a Gamecock baseball player, the college kid who dreamt of being drafted, and the minor leaguer who had his eyes set on making it to the show would be beyond proud too. Hudson, Hayes and I are so lucky to have been part of the baseball journey and watch you compete at the highest level. 

Though baseball has been beyond good to us, I can’t wait to see what our future has in store. So happy retirement ⚾️ I love you so much and the best is yet to come!! 🍾

Thank you to everyone who’s cheered on Grayson throughout his career and shown our family love and support 💛

Peace out, Preschool ✌🏻 Can’t believe our big boy is off to kindergarten this fall!! We’re so proud of Hudson 💛 He is witty, hilarious, and has almost passed me up in math already. We have no doubts he will thrive in elementary school and beyond ⭐️ #preschoolgraduation
